CEZ, Czech Steelmakers Save 10.5 Million CO2 Credits, Lidove Say

-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 
2011-05-03T06:14:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/cez-czech-steelmakers-save-10-5-million-co2-credits-lidove-noviny-says.html
CEZ AS (CEZ)  and Czech steelmakers such as
 ArcelorMittal (MT)  Ostrava saved 10.5 million carbon dioxide credits
worth 4 billion koruna ($246 million) last year which they can
resell or use in the future, Lidove Noviny reported, citing
European Commission records.  CEZ saved credits worth almost 700 million koruna in the
Czech Republic and a similar amount in Poland, the newspaper
said. ArcelorMittal Ostrava saved credits worth almost 800
million koruna, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  